text: Interstate 11 (I-11) is an Interstate Highway that currently runs for on the northwestâ€“southeast part in the U.S. state of Nevada, running concurrently with either or both U.S. Route 93 (US 93) and U.S. Route 95 (US 95) between the Arizona state line and Las Vegas. The freeway is planned to run from Nogales, Arizona to Fernley, Nevada near Reno and Sparks, generally following the current routes of I-19, I-10, US 93, US 95, US 50 and US 50 ALT. ==References== 11
